    <p>If this trend continues, what percentage of all income will the top <m>1</m>% have in the year 2030? If we model data in the chart with the blue line, we can estimate the value to be <m>27.6</m>%. This is one way math is used in real life.</p>

    <p> This section's main concept is <term>linear equation</term>, which often looks like <men>y=2x+1</men> What does each part in this equation mean? In this lesson, we will explore linear equations based on a table of data.</p>
  </subsection>

