    <p>Now, imagine the table's function is to take an input, and then gives an output. For example, in the first table, when the input is <q>black</q>, the output is <q>white</q>. The first table's function is to output a word with opposite meaning of the input word.</p>

  	<p>The third table's function is to take a number as input, and gives twice of that number as output. An easier way to describe the pattern is <m>y=2x</m>, where <m>x</m> represents the input, and <m>y</m> represents the output. Let's make the third table more mathematical:</p>

